{"title": "Letters of Oscar Wilde, Volume 1 (1868-1890)", "description": "This first collection of the correspondence of Oscar Wilde begins with the Irish playwright's earliest extant letter, thanking his mother for the hamper she had sent to him at school. It includes letters about his travels in Italy, his American lecture tour, the staging of his first play (Vera, or the Nihilists), arrangements for the publication of a friend's poetry collection, and exchanges in the press with artist James McNeill Whistler. The letters, some of which have been excerpted or redacted, are sourced from auction catalogues, newspapers, biographies, and other texts in the public domain. For a complete collection of Wilde's letters, please see \"The Complete Letters of Oscar Wilde,\" (2000) edited by Merlin Holland and Rupert Hart-Davis. - Summary by Rob Marland", "duration": 8187, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "114", "name": "Oscar Wilde"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/lettersofoscarwilde1_2007_librivox/wildeletters1_2007.jpg", "copyright_year": "0", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Literary Collections"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Rob Marland"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Rob Marland"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Julian Pratley"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "To Lady Jane Wilde, 8 Sept. 1868", "readers": [8164], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lettersofoscarwilde1_2007_librivox/letters1_01_wilde_64kb.mp3", "duration": 114}, {"section": 2, "title": "To Sir William Wilde and Lady Jane Wilde, c. 1875", "readers": [8164], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lettersofoscarwilde1_2007_librivox/letters1_02_wilde_64kb.mp3", "duration": 887}, {"section": 3, "title": "To Lady Jane Wilde", "readers": [8164], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lettersofoscarwilde1_2007_librivox/letters1_03_wilde_64kb.mp3", "duration": 51}, {"section": 4, "title": "